    "lifecycle_state": "Author draft",
    "details": {
      "en": {
        "id": "en",
        "purpose": "To estimate the volume of donor RBCs needed for RBC exchange in patients with sickle cell disease.",
        "keywords": [
          "RBC",
          "Sickle Cell",
          "Exchange",
          "donor"
        ],
        "use": "Use in patients with sickle cell disease complications requiring RBC exchange.\nVariables: \n- Patient sex: Feamle, Male\n- Patient height, cm\n- Patient weight, kg\n- Patient hematocrit, %\n- Patient's initial HgbS, %\n- Goal HgbS, %\n- Hematocrit of transfused RBCs, %\n\nFormula: \n\nTotal blood volume:\n- Male = [ 0.3669 × (height, m)3 + 0.03219 × (weight, kg) + 0.6041 ] \n- Female = [ 0.3561 × (height, m)3 + 0.03308 × (weight, kg) + 0.1833 ]\n\nRBC replacement volume = RBC volume × ln (HbS, initial / HbS, goal) / donor Hct\nWhere  RBC volume, mL = total blood volume, mL × hematocrit / 100\n\nNote: HbS and Hct are in whole % (i.e., 30%, not 0.3). RBC units assume 350 mL per unit and are rounded up to the nearest whole unit.",
        "copyright": "@CambioCDS"
      }
    },
    "other_details": {
      "references": "1. Brecher ME, Shaz BH, Schwartz J. Look This Up, Too! A Quick Reference in Apheresis. 3rd Ed. AABB Press, Bethesda MD 2013."
    }
  },
